  "prompt": "What are the jersey numbers of famous soccer players?",
  "response": "Famous soccer players have been associated with specific jersey numbers, often becoming iconic over time. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **Lionel Messi** - Throughout most of his career at FC Barcelona and currently at Paris Saint-Germain, Messi is famous for wearing the number **10**.\n\n2. **Cristiano Ronaldo** - Known for the number **7**, which he wore at Manchester United, Real Madrid, and currently again at Manchester United. He also wore number 7 at Juventus and the Portuguese national team.\n\n3. **Diego Maradona** - Wore the number **10** jersey during his legendary career, most famously with the Argentine national team and Napoli.\n\n4. **Pel\u00e9** - The Brazilian legend also donned the number **10**, becoming synonymous with the number during his time at Santos and the Brazil national team.\n\n5. **Zinedine Zidane** - Wore the number **10** for France and Real Madrid. During his time at Juventus, he wore number 21.\n\n6. **David Beckham** - Known for number **7** at Manchester United, although he wore number 23 at Real Madrid and the LA Galaxy.\n\n7. **Neymar Jr.** - Famously wears the number **10** for both Brazil and Paris Saint-Germain, though he wore number 11 at Barcelona.\n\n8. **Eric Cantona** - Known for wearing the number **7** jersey at Manchester United.\n\n9. **Ra\u00fal Gonz\u00e1lez** - The Spanish forward was known for his number **7** jersey at Real Madrid.\n\n10. **Ronaldinho** - Typically associated with the number **10**, wore it during his time at Barcelona and with the Brazilian national team.\n\n11. **Kylian Mbapp\u00e9** - Currently wears number **7** for Paris Saint-Germain but often wears number **10** for the French national team.\n\n12. **Francesco Totti** - Known for wearing the number **10** at AS Roma throughout his career.\n\nThese numbers are often chosen for their cultural significance, particularly the number 10, which is historically worn by some of the game's greatest playmakers and forwards.",
